PEOPLE of the STATE of CALIFORNIA, Plaintiff-Appellee, v. William DUCKETTE, Defendant-Appellant. No. 26167. United States Court of Appeals, Ninth Circuit. Feb. 4, 1971. Rehearing Denied March 1, 1971. Monty G. Mason II, Van Nuys, Cal., for appellant. Roger Arnebergh, City Atty., Michael T. Sauer, Asst. City Atty., Howard Fox, *456Deputy City Atty., Los Angeles, Cal., for appellee.

Before CHAMBERS, MERRILL and DUNIWAY, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM:

The order remanding the case to the state court is affirmed. Georgia v. Rachel, 1966, 384 U.S. 780, 86 S.Ct. 1783, 16 L.Ed.2d 925; Greenwood v. Peacock, 1966, 384 U.S. 808, 86 S.Ct. 1800, 16 L.Ed.2d 944; California v. Sandoval, 9 Cir., 1970, 434 F.2d 635.
